stylometry: Standard deviation is important because it determines the variation of the distribution scale and how far it is from the average.  If the standard deviation is low then that means the scale is very spread out and the highest and lowest numbers are very far from the average.  If the standard deviation is high then that means the scale is smaller and numbers are very close to the average.  The standard deviation can help a company determine a weak employees because if their sales performance is much lower on the scale they can see how much impact they are having on the overall average performance. If they are pulling the average down too much then they can be fired.
